Remedies
 
Section 17.             .  No delay, extension of time, renewal, compromise, or other indulgence which may occur or be granted by Parent under this Agreement from time to time shall impair Parents' rights or powers under this Agreement.  Parent shall not be deemed to have waived any of its rights under this Agreement, unless Parent shall have signed such a waiver in writing.  No such written waiver shall be effective as to any transactions or events of default occurring subsequent to the date of such waiver unless expressly so provided therein.
Waiver
 
