In April 2002, a joint venture was formed to renovate, operate, and maintain an existing water plant for 20 years so as to improve the quality and quantity of treated water supplied by the plant, for which the Company owns a 52% equity interest. The joint venture has a contractual life of 20 years, during which time services for 100% of the plant's output, treated wastewater, are purchased by the Municipality of Tianjin in the People's Republic of China via an exclusive service agreement. As of September 28, 2007, September 29, 2006, and September 30, 2005, the joint venture had equity earnings of $1.9 million, $1.9 million, and $1.8 million, respectively. The aggregate maximum exposure to loss as a result of the Company's involvement with this joint venture is limited to the equity investment, which is $22.9 million as of September 28, 2007.
                 
 
