Allocation of Expenses
 
  In the ordinary course of business, the Parent sweeps cash from the Company's bank accounts, and the Company maintains certain balances due to or from the Parent. Certain of the advances between the Company and the Parent are interest bearing. The Company had net interest (income) expense on intercompany loans from Tyco of $(14.3) million, $23.0 million, and $19.3 million for the years ended September 28, 2007, September 29, 2006, and September 30, 2005, respectively.
