  The obligation of the Company to prepay Notes pursuant to any offer required by subparagraph (c) and accepted in accordance with subparagraph (d) of this is subject to the occurrence of the Change in Control Prepayment Event in respect of which such offer and acceptances shall have been made.  In the event that such Change in Control Prepayment Event has not occurred on the Proposed Prepayment Date in respect thereof, the prepayment shall be deferred until, and shall be made on, the date on which such Change in Control Prepayment Event occurs.  The Company shall keep each holder of Notes reasonably and timely informed of (i) any such deferral of the date of prepayment, (ii) the date on which such Change in Control Prepayment Event and the prepayment are expected to occur, and (iii) any determination by the Company that efforts to effect the Change in Control giving rise to a Change in Control Prepayment Event have ceased or been abandoned (in which case the offers and acceptances made pursuant to this in respect of such Change in Control shall be deemed rescinded).
